    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2557893856" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2557893856" />
    <a title="Lauren " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1291915-lauren"><img alt="Lauren " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1643729278p2/1291915.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2557893856?book_show_action=true">Feb 28, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lauren " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lauren " href="/user/show/1291915-lauren">Lauren </a>
      </span>

          added it


          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781590173022" href="/book/show/6145869-season-of-migration-to-the-north">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1291915-lauren?shelf=east-africa-lit">east-africa-lit</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1291915-lauren?shelf=translated-works">translated-works</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1291915-lauren?shelf=rtw21">rtw21</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1291915-lauren?shelf=best-of-2021">best-of-2021</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1291915-lauren?shelf=1960s-fiction">1960s-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1291915-lauren?shelf=arab-arabic-lit">arab-arabic-lit</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2557893856" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3490680780329200291"><i>&quot;I was furious - I won&apos;t disguise the fact from you - when the man laughed unashamedly and said &apos;We have no need of poetry here. It would have been better if you&apos;d studies agriculture, engineering, or medicine.&apos; Look at the way he says &apos;we&apos; and does not include me, and does not include me, though he knows that this is my village and that it is he - not I - who is the stranger.&quot;</i><br/><br/>▫️ SEASON OF MIGRATION TO THE NORTH by Tayeb Salih, translated from the Arabic by Denys Johnson-Davies, 1966/1969.<br/>#Readt</span>
  <span id="freeText3490680780329200291" style="display:none"><i>"I was furious - I won't disguise the fact from you - when the man laughed unashamedly and said 'We have no need of poetry here. It would have been better if you'd studies agriculture, engineering, or medicine.' Look at the way he says 'we' and does not include me, and does not include me, though he knows that this is my village and that it is he - not I - who is the stranger."</i><br /><br />▫️ SEASON OF MIGRATION TO THE NORTH by Tayeb Salih, translated from the Arabic by Denys Johnson-Davies, 1966/1969.<br />#ReadtheWorld21 📍Sudan<br /><br />Stunning prose that drew me in from the first paragraph. Long on the shelf and now *finally* read and appreciated. Hailed as one of the best modern Arabic novels, and Tayeb Salih's most well-known work, this was even more than I was expecting.<br /><br />Exploration of dichotomies:<br />North / South<br />Metropole / Colony<br />Male / Female<br />Mustafa Sa'eed / Unnamed Narrator<br /><br />✒️ Salih and Johnson-Davies worked together on this English translation (according to the intro, and Johnson-Davies' memoir). It's quite refreshing to learn about the close collaboration since I loved the writing style so much.<br /><br />I see the "reverse" Heart of Darkness theme here, as well as Shakespearean #Othello - two oft-quoted comparisons to SEASON. Also see some Naguib Mahfouz, but that could be because Mahfouz and Salih were from neighboring spaces, two African Arabic writers of the same era... Or it could be because they share a translator in Denys Johnson-Davies. Either way, the salon-style conversations reminded me of Mahfouz's ADRIFT ON THE NILE...<br /><br />🎧 Followed my reading of this with a great radio interview with Salih. Available to listen on CBC Radio, Writers &amp; Company - "Tayeb Salih on Culture and Conflict in Sudan". Recorded in 2002, before Salih's passing in 2009. Recommended if you want to learn more about Sudan, role of memory in his work, and Salih's praxis. <br /><br />Absolutely will be reading more Salih. The Wedding of Zein and other stories, and his newly (2020) translated essays "Mansi, A Rare Man in His Own Way" await.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3490680780329200291" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


