<div id="review_2379963934" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2379963934" />
    <a title="Serge (on a semi-hiatus)" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/31127520-serge-on-a-semi-hiatus"><img alt="Serge (on a semi-hiatus)" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1642536913p2/31127520.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2379963934?book_show_action=true">May 02, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Serge (on a semi-hiatus)" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Serge (on a semi-hiatus)" href="/user/show/31127520-serge-on-a-semi-hiatus">Serge (on a semi-hiatus)</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/31127520-serge-on-a-semi-hiatus?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2379963934" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7976811136237501986">This book did a really good job describing colonialism and the cultural and emotional effect it has on the citizens of a country. Even though this seems to be the main theme of the book, it is just one of the many layers of the complexity of the overall story, which describes Mustafa Said’s almost sadistic urge to “conquer England” through his sexual adventures with British women. After a turbulent period in England, which ends in murder and a prison sentence, he returns to his homeland in Sudan</span>
  <span id="freeText7976811136237501986" style="display:none">This book did a really good job describing colonialism and the cultural and emotional effect it has on the citizens of a country. Even though this seems to be the main theme of the book, it is just one of the many layers of the complexity of the overall story, which describes Mustafa Said’s almost sadistic urge to “conquer England” through his sexual adventures with British women. After a turbulent period in England, which ends in murder and a prison sentence, he returns to his homeland in Sudan, which is where the narrator meets him and explores Mustafa’s complex personality which is masked under a very simplistic and mellow demeanour. Personally, my favourite elements of the book were the way life in a Sudanese village is described in all its’ oriental/traditional simplicity, and the beautifully descriptive literary style of Tayeb Saleh which leaves the reader wanting to read more and see what happens next. Definitely worth the read, and it left me curious about reading more books by the author. </span>
  <a data-text-id="7976811136237501986" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


